
** Lokal Partitioned Indexes

  - For OLTP systems local partitioned indexes preferred
  - They correspondent to the table partition

** Global Partitioned Indexes

  - Range
  - Hash

A global partitioned index is normally not equipartitioned with the
underlying table.

** Partition pruning

*** Execution Plan

  - PSTART, PSTOP (dbms_xplan.display)
  - If KEY in PSTART and PSTOP then dynamic pruning is used


  - partition range single (TRUE)
  - partition range all    (FALSE)

*** Dictionary Tables

  - user_part_tables
  - user_part_key_columns

